  "text": "miRNA RT-qPCR RNA was isolated as described above. 20-30 ng total RNA were used for reverse transcription (RT) if not indicated otherwise. RT reactions were performed with ABI's TaqMan MicroRNA RT kit (Cat No 4366596) according to the manufacturer except for using only 50% of the recommended volumes for the Applied Biosystems kits. PCR reactions were performed on 1 ml RT product with 50% of the recommended volumes for ABI reagents. As indicated, for some experiments primers and probes were designed as described [CITATION_1] and ordered from Integrated DNA Technologies (IDT) using the following sequences: http://urology. ucsf.edu/blellochlab/protocols/miRNAqPCRsequences.txt. Annealing temperatures for IDT reactions were: mmu-miR10a, mmu-miR-16, mmu-miR-155, hsa-miR-155:47.5uC. All reactions were normalized to sno202, measured with the ABI kit mouse snoRNA202 TaqMan assay, identification # 1232, (Cat No 4380914).",
